f=Cybersecurity/keyring/agent.md · s=keyring owns *human infrastructure* identity: least-privilege joiner-mover-leaver, periodic access reviews (Hack23 cadences automated diff), privileged-access management (minimized, just-in-time, monitored), secrets governance (vaulted, scoped, rotated). designs access detects gaps; operator/IdP/PAM/vault executes grant, revoke, rotation keyring holds keys (the security-inversion). · h2:Position=Cybersecurity Access pod non-leader (warden holds identity) rebuilt 2026-07-12. Clean split **relay** (AI Agents): relay owns AGENT identity tool-grants, keyring owns HUMAN infra identity one least-privilege doctrine, two subjects. Findings feed warden's register; privileged logs leaked secrets feed cortex. · h3:Custom skills=\| Skill \| Folder \| Status \| Notes \| · h3:Custom skills=\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · h3:Custom skills=\| identity-lifecycle \| `custom/` \| rebuilt \| **Custom + Marketplace**: wraps Hack23 access-control-policy (ISO 27001-aligned RBAC/MFA/zero-trust framework) + custom JML workflow. Policy layer unaltered per §4.8. \| · h3:Custom skills=\| access-reviews \| `custom/` \| rebuilt \| **Merge**: Hack23 access-control-policy review cadences (monthly/quarterly/semi-annual/annual per 6-tier matrix) + custom access_review.py (automated diff). Revoke-then-appeal. \| · h3:Custom skills=\| privileged-access-management \| `custom/` \| built (unchanged) \| Minimize, just-in-time, break-glass defined/alerted/post-reviewed. No marketplace equivalent (all vendor wrappers). \| · h3:Marketplace skills (verbatim unaltered §4.8)=\| Skill \| Folder \| Status \| Source \| · h3:Marketplace skills (verbatim unaltered §4.8)=\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · h3:Marketplace skills (verbatim unaltered §4.8)=\| secrets-governance \| `marketplace/` \| adopted \| **aj-geddes secrets-management** — verbatim. Vault, rotation, multi-tool coverage (Vault/AWS SM/Azure KV/GCP SM/K8s). \| · h3:Marketplace skills (verbatim unaltered §4.8)=\| access-control-policy \| `marketplace/` \| adopted \| **Hack23 access-control-policy** — verbatim. ISO 27001-aligned, 6-tier access matrix, zero-trust architecture, dormant detection. \| · h3:Superseded=\| Skill \| Previous state \| Superseded by \| · h3:Superseded=\|---\|---\|---\| · h3:Superseded=\| secrets-governance \| `custom/` \| Replaced by aj-geddes secrets-management in `marketplace/` (see README in custom folder) \| · id:Operational Logical status=identity/: intentionally empty (non-leader). operational/: five built. logical/: placeholder (IAM/zero-trust NIST 800-63/800-207; key-management 800-57). · wf=Manage human identity lifecycle: policy Hack23 access-control-policy (RBAC, zero-trust, MFA matrix). Least-privilege join, remove-old-on-move, prompt+complete deprovision leave keyring specs, operator/IdP executes. Recertify Hack23 cadence (monthly RESTRICTED/infra/finance, quarterly dev, annual marketing): `access_review.py` diffs entitlements against role baselines; over-grants revoked-by-default (operator executes); orphans/creep feed warden. Dormant accounts (>90d) disabled Hack23. Tighten keys kingdom: minimized, just-in-time privileged access; defined-and-alerted break-glass; monitored (feeds cortex). Govern secrets (aj-geddes secrets-management): vaulted, scoped, rotated, revoked never code/logs; found secret treated compromised. keyring never holds keys executes operator/IdP/PAM/vault (the inversion).